==English==

===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, alteration of earlier {{m|enm|hendi||handy, skillful}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hendiġ||skillful}} (as in {{m|ang|listhendiġ||skilled in art}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*handugaz||handy, skillful, nimble}}, from {{m|gem-pro|*handuz||hand}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|hand|y|nocat=1}}. Cognate with {{cog|gml|handich||skillful, apt}}, {{cog|gmh|handec}}, {{m|gmh|hendec||manual, hand-held}}, {{cog|non|hǫndugr||efficient}}, {{cog|got|𐌷𐌰𐌽𐌳𐌿𐌲𐍃||wise, clever}}. Akin to {{cog|nl|handig||handy}}, {{cog|no|hendig||handy}}, {{cog|sv|händig||handy}}.

